SIMPLE: glider
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Glider
<hw>Glid"er</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>One who,
or that which, glides.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>a heavier-than-air flying machine similar to an
airplane, but without an engine. It is typically towed to a high
altitide by a powered aircraft and then glides to earth with no other
source of power.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>a type of seat used on porches or in gardens, which
is mounted on a frame so that it may glide forward and
backward.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Glide slope</ent>⟦br⟧
